MORPC staff generates annual population estimates for MORPC member governments for the purpose of dues assessments. The estimates are then adopted by the MORPC Board after each government has had an opportunity to review them. The estimation method is based on the number of new housing units and takes into account each jurisdiction's vacancy rate and population per household as reported by the US Census Bureau.

This sidewalk dataset is a comprehensive transportation network of over 221,000 features representing existing sidewalks, existing crosswalks (marked/unmarked), and sidewalk gaps and matches the cardinality of unique Location-Based Reference System (LBRS) road centerline databases for Franklin, Delaware, Fairfield, and Licking Counties in Ohio. All data was digitized in Esri ArcGIS 10.2.1 software in the Ohio South State Plane (NAD 83), feet projection. This sidewalk inventory is intended for planning purposes only. TranSystems does not warrant the accurateness of the sidewalks or crosswalks depicted in this dataset. None of the sidewalk or crosswalk segments have been field verified. Every reasonable effort has been made to reflect the correct GIS segmentation of all sidewalks, crosswalks, and sidewalk gaps. MORPC will facilitate the maintenance of this data by engaging local governments.

**Change URL to https when loading layer to web map.U.S. EPA defines a Sole Source Aquifer (SSA) as an aquifer that supplies at least 50 percent of the drinking water consumed in the area overlying the aquifer. These areas may have no alternative drinking water source(s) that could physically, legally and economically supply all those who depend on the aquifer for drinking water.The SSA designation protects an area's ground water resource by requiring U.S. EPA to review certain proposed projects within the designated area. All proposed projects receiving federal funds are subject to review to ensure that they do not endanger the water source.For more information on SSAs,?including GIS data, visit?http://water.epa.gov/infrastructure/drinkingwater/sourcewater/protection/solesourceaquifer.cfm.
